h3. Issue Summary
Using the REST API endpoint *Get filter* {code}/rest/api/3/filter/{id}{code}, returns a malformed answer for the *searchUrl* key.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a filter in Jira;
 # Get the filter id by looking at the URL;
 # Run the following REST API endpoint:
{code}https://<instance-name>.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/filter/<filter-id>{code}

h3. Expected Results
The *searchURL* should return something in the form of:
{code}"searchUrl": "https://<instance-name>.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/search?jql=<jql-query>"{code}

h3. Actual Results
The *searchURL* return as:
{code}"searchUrl": "https://<instance-name>.atlassian.net/rest/search?jql=<jql-query>"{code}
The URL is missing the */api/3* string between "rest" and "search".

h3. Workaround
Inserting manually or programmatically the */api/3* string between "rest" and "search" on the *searchURL* returned.

h3. Issue Summary
When having a table in the issue description that has inside its cell a line of text followed by an extra space and a bullet list, the cloning process fails.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 * Create an issue
 * Create a table within the description
 * In one of its cells, write one line of text and add an extra space at the end
 * Press Enter, and create a bullet list
 * Add at least one item on the list
 * Clone the issue
Video: https://cl.ly/ccf2c85216cd

h3. Expected Results
The issue will be cloned successfully.

