h3. Workaround
# Make sure to not leave an extra space at the end of the first line of the cell;
# Copy and paste the text of the description after the cloning process is done;

In the old comment renderer you were able to generate tables by pasting in formatted plaintext like so: 
{code:java}
|| A | B |
|| C | D |{code}
However this feature no longer exists in the updated Jira comments view. Is there planned support for pasting markdown like tables and having them rendered in the fabric comment? Or is this feature not coming to the new issue view?

h3. Suggestion
Allow the ability to format sentences using color syntax
eg. 
{code}
<span style="color:red;">hello there</span>
{code}{code}
<font color=red>hello there</font>
{code}

On the new issue view, the local file markup is not available. If we try to use the markup suggested on [Text Formatting Notation Help|https://jira.atlassian.com/secure/WikiRendererHelpAction.jspa?section=links] it does not render properly, despite it does on the old issue view. Right below it follows the referred markup:
{noformat}
[file:///c:/temp/foo.txt]
{noformat}
h3. Workaround

There is no current work around.
